# Figma Design-System Rules (mbn-theme)

How to translate Figma designs into this WordPress/Gutenberg theme via the Figma MCP.
Read this **before** calling `get_design_context` / `get_variable_defs` / `download_assets`.
The theme has no React/CSS-Modules/Storybook front end — it renders **native
server-rendered Gutenberg blocks styled with Tailwind + `--mbn-*` CSS variables**. Map
Figma primitives onto the constructs below; do **not** invent a parallel token or
component system.

---

## 1. Token Definitions

**Single source of truth:** the `mbn_settings` WordPress option (Appearance → **MBN
Theme**, not the Customizer). Sanitizers + emitters live in
`inc/includes-theme-settings.php`; `mbn_build_css_variables()` prints a `<style>` block
of `--mbn-*` variables into `:root` (front end + editor canvas).

- **Format:** runtime CSS custom properties, not a JSON token file. There is **no
  Style Dictionary / token-transform build.** Figma variables map to `--mbn-*` vars:

| Figma token | Theme variable | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Color styles / variables | `--mbn-color-scheme-1..8` | stored as hex in settings, **emitted as `rgba()`** via `mbn_hex_to_rgba()`; also `--mbn-color-primary`/`--mbn-color-secondary` |
| Primary/display font | `--mbn-font-primary` | from the **WordPress Fonts Library** (custom-installed families only) |
| Body font | `--mbn-font-secondary` | |
| Fallback | `--mbn-font-fallback` | `@font-face` with `size-adjust`/`ascent`/`descent`/`line-gap` overrides |
| Heading sizes | `--mbn-size-h1..h6`, `--mbn-size-body` | **responsive**: mobile base in `:root`, tablet `@media(min-width:768px)`, desktop `@media(min-width:1024px)` (`mbn_build_typography_media()`) |
| Heading weights | `--mbn-weight-h1..h6`, `--mbn-weight-body` | |
| Container | `--mbn-container-width` | |
| Corner radius | `--mbn-radius` (+ `.mbn-radius` utility) | |

- **Tablet/mobile heading sizes auto-reduce** from the desktop value, never below the
  paragraph size; the paragraph size stays fixed (`mbn_scale_typography_size()`).
- **When importing Figma tokens:** update the `mbn_settings` option / preset UI (or the
  `/build-design` flow drives the preset from the design). Never hardcode a Figma hex or
  px size into a block when a `--mbn-*` variable exists.

