## 4. Asset Management

- **Every design asset (images, backgrounds, videos, vectors, icons) lives in the WP
  media library** — referenced from media, **never raw Figma URLs, never committed in
  the theme.** Use `download_assets` → upload via WordPress MCP / WP-CLI (dedupe; never
  re-upload existing media).
- **Raster images:** render with `wp_get_attachment_image()` /
  `get_the_post_thumbnail()` at a size from a **per-image size attribute** (responsive
  `srcset`+`sizes`, lazy-load). Expose an **image-size dropdown** via the shared
  `MediaPicker` `sizeValue`/`onSizeChange` props (default `full`). Storage convention:
  single image → `imageSize`; extra/logo → `<name>Size`; repeater → `withSize:true`
  stored in `<key>Size`.
- **Section / full-bleed backgrounds are a responsive CSS `background-image`, not an
  `<img>`** — use `mbn_responsive_bg( $element_id, $attachment_id, $lcp, $position )`
  (`inc/block-layout-helpers.php`). It prints a scoped `<style>` swapping the image by
  breakpoint (mobile → `medium_large`, ≥768px → `large`, ≥1280px → `full`,
  `background-size:cover`). Wrapper gets a unique id (`wp_unique_id('mbn-…-')`) +
  `bg-cover bg-center`.
- **LCP:** one section-background block per page carries an "LCP (above the fold)"
  toggle (`LcpControl` → `lcp` attr); pass `$lcp = true` to preload it. Content `<img>`
  LCP → `mbn_lcp_img_attrs()`.
- **Optimization:** new JPEG/PNG uploads auto-generate **WebP** sub-sizes
  (`optimizations.php`); `wp_get_attachment_image()` serves WebP automatically. No CDN
  config in-theme.
- **Background video:** `<video autoplay muted loop playsinline>` + **mandatory preload
  `<img>` poster** (shown until ready / on reduced-motion). Front-end lazy loader
  `assets/js/mbn-video.js` (`data-src` → `src`, IntersectionObserver).

