## 5. Icon System

- **Icons & vectors are SVG, stored in the WP media library** (not an icon font, not a
  sprite, not a committed `icons/` dir).
- **SVGs are inlined as `<svg>`** (never a background, never `<img>`) via
  `mbn_inline_svg_attachment( $attachment_id, $size, $classes )`
  (`inc/block-layout-helpers.php`) — `$size = 0` omits width/height so CSS controls it:

  ```php
  echo mbn_inline_svg_attachment( $accent_id, 0, 'block h-[12px] w-full' ); // phpcs:ignore ...
  ```

- Strip baked icon background paths on export (see the figma skill). The `mbn-ai-icon`
  component wraps icon usage; a per-icon size attribute controls dimensions.
- No naming convention beyond the media slug; look up by slug with
  `mbn_attachment_id_by_slug()` when needed.

