## 6. Styling Approach

- **Tailwind utilities only** — for admin/editor **and** front end. Global entry
  `resources/css/app.css` → built to `assets/build/tailwind.css`
  (`npm run build:css`). Component-layer globals live in `@layer components` there
  (e.g. `.wp-block-button__link`, scroll-reveal `[data-mbn-reveal]`, sticky-header
  `.mbn-site-header`).
- **NO attribute styling. Never use `style="…"`.** Use Tailwind utilities, design-system
  classes, and `--mbn-*` vars. If custom CSS is unavoidable, put it in a scoped
  `<style>` inside the block's `render.php` (scoped by an `mbn-` class/id). *(Editor
  inspector controls in `edit.js` may use inline `style` for admin-only spacing — that's
  React admin UI, not front-end output.)*
- **Design-system utilities** (safelisted in `tailwind.config.js`): `bg-scheme-N` /
  `text-scheme-N` / `border-scheme-N` (1–8), `bg/text/border-mbn-primary|secondary`,
  `font-primary` / `font-secondary`, `text-mbn-h1..h6` / `text-mbn-body`, `rounded-mbn`,
  `max-w-mbn-container`. Map Figma color/type styles to these, not to raw hex/px.
- **Custom classes:** `mbn-` prefix, kebab-case, no `__`/`_`. Add one only when
  utilities can't express it.
- **Responsive:** mobile-first Tailwind breakpoints. Verify desktop **1920×1080** and
  mobile **Moto G Power 360×640**. Match the design's **font weights**, borders,
  vectors, column ratios, hovers, sticky header, scroll behavior.
- **Runtime-built arbitrary values:** Tailwind only compiles `bg-[#e50b07]`,
  `h-[3px]`, `opacity-[0.4]` when it sees the **exact literal** in a scanned file, and
  safelist *regex patterns can't match arbitrary values*. When a `render.php`
  concatenates a class from a **dynamic** value (hex/px/opacity), the palette + bounded
  ranges are enumerated as explicit strings by `mbnArbitrarySafelist` in
  `tailwind.config.js`. **Add a new hex to `MBN_ARBITRARY_PALETTE`** (or widen a range)
  so it compiles — never rely on a pattern. Literal arbitrary classes (e.g.
  `shadow-[0px_3px_0px_#d3110e]`) need no safelist (they appear verbatim).
- **One shared container:** header, footer, and `post_content` use the same container
  (`.container` / `max-w-mbn-container` + `px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`) so edges align.

