## 7. Project Structure

```
mbn-theme/
├── src/                      # block source (JSX)
│   ├── <section>/            #   composite/section blocks: mbn-ai-hero, mbn-ai-faq …
│   │   ├── block.json  index.js  edit.js  render.php
│   ├── components/<name>/    #   reusable mbn-ai- component blocks (mbn-ai-button …)
│   ├── shared/               #   MediaPicker, controls, items-repeater, tag-control,
│   │                         #   lcp-control, animation-control, server-preview, layout…
│   ├── mbn-section|container|columns|column/   # layout primitives
│   ├── mbn-logo | mbn-menu   #   dynamic server-rendered blocks
│   └── template-reuse | content-io/  # editor-plugin sidebars (not blocks)
├── build/                    # generated (gitignored) — block-registry.php scans this
├── inc/                      # theme PHP: theme-settings (tokens), block-layout-helpers,
│                             #   block-templates, template-reuse, media-uploads, content-io
├── resources/css/app.css     # Tailwind entry  →  assets/build/tailwind.css
├── tailwind.config.js        # theme(--mbn vars) + safelist + arbitrary-value enum
├── optimizations.php         # auto-WebP sub-sizes
├── block-registry.php        # recursively registers every build/**/block.json
├── header.php / footer.php    # fall back to header/footer BLOCK TEMPLATES (do_blocks)
└── .claude/                  # SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for AI rules/skills/commands
```

- **Header/footer** render from `header`/`footer` **block templates** via
  `mbn_render_part_template()` (do_blocks), falling back to `header.php`/`footer.php`.
  Block templates are the `mbn_block_template` CPT (`inc/includes-block-templates.php`).
- **Feature organization:** one directory per block; shared logic in `src/shared/`
  (JS) and `inc/` (PHP helpers). AI-authored work is namespaced `mbn-ai-`.
- **Content moves as JSON, not chat pastes:** `inc/includes-content-io.php` exports/
  imports a post + its media (upsert keyed by `post_id`, media matched by filename).
  In the editor it's the **Import / Export sidebar** (icon beside Remote Templates;
  import always targets the CURRENT post); also `wp mbn-content export|import` and
  `GET|POST /wp-json/mbn/v1/posts` — see `development.md`.

