## Conventions & guardrails (must-follow)

- Functions/vars `snake_case`; classes `PascalCase`; constants `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`.
- **Sanitize all input, escape all output** (`esc_html`/`esc_attr`/`esc_url`/
  `wp_kses_post`); intentionally-raw block output carries a scoped
  `phpcs:ignore WordPress.Security.EscapeOutput…` with a reason. Never hardcode secrets.
- **Every media field uses the shared `MediaPicker`** (thumbnail for images, inline
  `<video>` for video) — never a bare `MediaUpload`. Every raster image has a size
  attribute + size dropdown (default `full`).
- **Use ALL shared controls from `src/shared/`** — `MediaPicker`, `ItemsRepeater`
  (multiple repeaters via `attribute`), `TagControl` for **every heading tag**
  (`*Tag` attr + `mbn_tag()` in render), `SizeControl`, `LcpControl`,
  `AnimationControl`, `ServerPreview`. Never re-implement one inline.
- **Maps:** the Google Maps API key lives in Appearance → MBN Theme → Integrations
  (`mbn_setting( 'maps_api_key' )`); map blocks offer `mapMode` google|image (Maps
  Embed API iframe with a static-image fallback) — never hardcode a key.
- **Inspector controls are spaced:** standard WP controls keep their default bottom
  margin (don't pass `__nextHasNoMarginBottom`); custom controls wrap in
  `<div className="mbn-control" style={{ marginBottom: 24 }}>`.
- **No hardcoded menus / link lists** — nav comes from Appearance → Menus.
- **`.claude/` is the source of truth.** Edit `.claude/**` only, then run
  `scripts/sync-ai-config.sh` to regenerate `.cursor/**` + `AGENTS.md` (a pre-commit
  hook enforces sync). **Never hand-edit `.cursor/**` or `AGENTS.md`.**
- **Run `npm run build`** after changing block source so editor + front end match.
- **Test before commit** (`composer run lint`); no direct `git push` — open a PR.
- **Figma → blocks workflow** is driven by the `figma` skill / `/build-design
  <post_id> <figma_link>` and `/build-components <figma_link>` commands. Browser QA runs
  **only** on request via `/testing <url>`.
